Set up serial debugging for {{device_type}} device.

Port: {{serial_port}}
Baud Rate: {{baud_rate}}
Log Level: {{log_level}}

Debug Configuration:
1. Open serial connection at {{serial_port}} with {{baud_rate}} baud
2. Configure log filtering for {{log_level}} and above
3. Enable timestamp prefixing
4. Set up output buffering for log capture

Debug Commands:
{{#if enable_commands}}
- Reset device: Send RST command
- Get status: Send STATUS command
- Configure: Send CONFIG command with parameters
{{/if}}

{{#if save_logs}}Save debug logs to {{log_file}}{{/if}}
